OF
MAGNETOAERODYNAMIC
EFFECTS
SOME
DATA
ON
CONDUCTIVITY
OF
PURE
AND
SEEDED
AIR
ARE
FIRST
EXAMINED
DIMENSIONLESS
QUANTITIES
REPRESENTING
THE
RATIOS
OF
FORCES
AND
OF
CURRENTS
ARE
THEN
FORMED
AND
THEIR
VALUES
STUDIED
FOR
CONDITIONS
OF
FLIGHT
IN
THE
ATMOSPHERE
SOME
